extends com.qualcomm.robotcore.eventloop.opmode.LinearOpMode

      • drive

        void drive(double power,
           int distance)
        Tells the robot to drive forward a set distance. Slows down as it gets closer to the set distance. Also corrects its self if using the gyro sensor if it starts to drift.
        Parameters:
        power - The maximum power the robot will drive.
        distance - The distance the robot should drive in cm.
        See Also:
        getGyroPowerAdjustment(), getDrivePower(double, double)

        private double getDrivePower(double driveDistance,
                             double power)
        Generates a parabolic function and slows the robot down while driving forwards or backwards using the parameters.
        Parameters:
        driveDistance - The distance that the robot is attempting to drive.
        power - The maximum power the robot should drive at.
        Returns:
        The power that the robot should drive at.

        void followBeaconLineToWall(double power,

        power - The maximum power the robot should drive at.
